-- OPEC Members May Earn $1.2 Trillion on Oil Exports, DOE Says
-- B y   L y n n   D o a n
-- 2012-04-13T23:53:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/opec-members-may-earn-1-2-trillion-on-oil-exports-doe-says-1-.html
OPEC members may earn $1.17
trillion in net revenue from oil exports this year, up 14
percent from 2011, the Energy Department said in a  report .  OPEC’s revenue from exporting oil may reach $1.13 trillion
in 2013, according to the federal Energy Information
Administration. Members of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries earned $1.03 trillion last year, a 33
percent increase from 2010, the agency said.  “ Saudi Arabia  earned the largest share of these earnings,
$312 billion, representing 30 percent of total OPEC revenues,”
the agency said.  The Energy Information Administration based the estimates
on short-term energy price projections. On a per capita basis
OPEC earnings reached $2,684 last year, the agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
